items.title: Awesome Machine Learning
items.content_text:
### Python / Computer Vision

*   [Detectron (⭐26k)](https://github.com/facebookresearch/Detectron) - FAIR's software system that implements state-of-the-art object detection algorithms, including Mask R-CNN. It is written in Python and powered by the Caffe2 deep learning framework. **\[Deprecated]**
*   [Detecto (⭐620)](https://github.com/alankbi/detecto) - Train and run a computer vision model with 5-10 lines of code.
items.content_html:
Python / Computer Vision

  • Detectron (⭐26k) - FAIR's software system that implements state-of-the-art object detection algorithms, including Mask R-CNN. It is written in Python and powered by the Caffe2 deep learning framework. [Deprecated]
  • Detecto (⭐620) - Train and run a computer vision model with 5-10 lines of code.

items.title: Awesome Actions
items.content_text:
### GitHub Tools and Management / Docker Container Actions

*   [Use private actions in any workflow (⭐169)](https://github.com/InVisionApp/private-action-loader)

### Utility / Docker Container Actions

*   [Read Properties (⭐23)](https://github.com/christian-draeger/read-properties) - Read values from `.properties` files.
*   [Write Properties (⭐14)](https://github.com/christian-draeger/write-properties) - Write values to `.properties` files.

### Utility / Environments

*   [Create an envfile (⭐462)](https://github.com/SpicyPizza/create-envfile)
*   [Export global environment variables for succeeding build steps (⭐6)](https://github.com/zweitag/github-actions)
*   [Programmatically set environment variables for use in subsequent steps (⭐51)](https://github.com/allenevans/set-env)

### Utility / Semantic Versioning

*   [Next SemVers (⭐59)](https://github.com/WyriHaximus/github-action-next-semvers) - Output the next version for major, minor, and patch version based on the given semver version.

### Static Analysis / Testing

*   [xUnit Slack Reporter: Sends summary of tests from xUnit reports to a Slack channel (⭐12)](https://github.com/ivanklee86/xunit-slack-reporter)
*   [Run codeception tests (⭐15)](https://github.com/joelwmale/codeception-action)
*   [Run TestCafe tests (⭐36)](https://github.com/DevExpress/testcafe-action)
*   [Run Unity tests (⭐232)](https://github.com/webbertakken/unity-test-runner)
*   [Run Cypress E2E tests (⭐1.4k)](https://github.com/cypress-io/github-action)
*   [Test Ansible roles with Molecule (⭐55)](https://github.com/robertdebock/molecule-action)

### Static Analysis / Linting

*   [Runs Hadolint against a Dockerfile within a repository (⭐13)](https://github.com/burdzwastaken/hadolint-action)

### Static Analysis / Security

*   [AWS Secrets Manager Actions (⭐63)](https://github.com/say8425/aws-secrets-manager-actions) - Define AWS Secrets Manager secrets to environment values.

### Static Analysis / Code Coverage

*   [Scan code with SonarCloud (⭐607)](https://github.com/sonarsource/sonarcloud-github-action)
*   [Send your code coverage to codecov.io (⭐1.6k)](https://github.com/codecov/codecov-action)
*   [Publishing code coverage to CodeClimate (⭐205)](https://github.com/paambaati/codeclimate-action)

### Monitoring / Code Coverage

*   [Audit a webpage with Google Chrome's Lighthouse tests (⭐347)](https://github.com/jakejarvis/lighthouse-action)
*   [Runs Lighthouse and posts results to PRs and Slack (⭐499)](https://github.com/foo-software/lighthouse-check-action)
*   [Run Lighthouse in CI using GitHub Actions (⭐1.2k)](https://github.com/treosh/lighthouse-ci-action)
*   [Continuous Benchmarking and Benchmark Visualization for Go (⭐150)](https://github.com/bobheadxi/gobenchdata)

### Deployment / Code Coverage

*   [Purge Cloudflare cache after updating a website (⭐139)](https://github.com/jakejarvis/cloudflare-purge-action)

### Deployment / Docker

*   [Update a Docker Hub repository description from README.md (⭐352)](https://github.com/peter-evans/dockerhub-description)
*   [Publish Docker Images to the GitHub Package Registry (GPR) (⭐55)](https://github.com/machine-learning-apps/gpr-docker-publish)
*   [Update a repository's "Full description" on Docker Hub (⭐4)](https://github.com/mpepping/github-actions/tree/master/docker-hub-metadata)

### Deployment / Kubernetes

*   [Deploy to any Cloud or Kubernetes Using Pulumi (⭐277)](https://github.com/pulumi/actions)
*   [Deploy to Kubernetes with kubectl (⭐218)](https://github.com/steebchen/kubectl)
*   [Get Kubeconfig File From Google Kubernetes Engine (GKE) (⭐13)](https://github.com/machine-learning-apps/gke-kubeconfig)

### Deployment / AWS

*   [Sync/upload a directory to an AWS S3 bucket (⭐1.1k)](https://github.com/jakejarvis/s3-sync-action)
*   [Deploy Lambda code to an existing function (⭐427)](https://github.com/appleboy/lambda-action)

### Deployment / Terraform

*   [Generate terraform documentation (⭐39)](https://github.com/Dirrk/terraform-docs) - Uses terraform-docs to generate docs for terraform modules.
*   [An example of using Terraform to validate and apply GitHub administration (⭐2)](https://github.com/asgharlabs/github-terraform/tree/master/.github/workflows)

### Build / Terraform

*   [run-cmake (⭐191)](https://github.com/lukka/run-cmake) - Multi platform action to build C/C++ software with [CMake](https://cmake.org) and [Ninja](https://ninja-build.org/).
*   [run-vcpkg (⭐215)](https://github.com/lukka/run-vcpkg) - Multi platform action to build and install C/C++ dependencies with [vcpkg (⭐25k)](https://github.com/microsoft/vcpkg).
*   [Build Go applications for multiplatform (⭐6)](https://github.com/izumin5210/action-go-crossbuild)
